---
description: Apply Docker and Docker Compose conventions for development. Use when modifying Docker-related files.
globs: compose.yml,.docker/**/*,Makefile,Dockerfile*
alwaysApply: false
---

Docker Compose v2:

- File: `compose.yml` (not `docker-compose.yml`)
- No `version:` field (deprecated)
- Use `depends_on` with `condition: service_healthy` when available
- Use named networks (`modelo-network`)

Dockerfile Patterns:

- Multi-stage builds: `deps` → `runtime`
- `oven/bun:1.3-alpine` for dependency installation stage
- `node:24-alpine` for runtime stage (Hono via @hono/node-server)
- `dos2unix` for Windows/WSL2 compatibility on entrypoints
- Mount `node_modules` as anonymous volume to avoid host conflicts
- `bun install --linker hoisted` inside Docker for reliable module resolution

Services:

- Traefik 3.6: reverse proxy, Docker + HTTP + File providers
- Keycloak 26.5: identity provider, realm import from .docker/keycloak/
- PostgreSQL 18 (pgvector/pgvector:pg18): primary database + vector extension
- Redis 8: sessions, cache, pub/sub (event bus streams)
- auth-api (3000), hub-shell (3001), app-registry (3002), entitlements (3003), feature-flags (3004)
- All Hub services route through Traefik on `*.modelo.dev`

Makefile Targets:

- `make up` / `make down` for compose lifecycle
- `make up-build` to rebuild and start
- `make logs` / `make logs-{service}` for logging
- `make shell-{service}` for shell access (auth, registry, entitlements, flags, ai, docs, hub, postgres, redis)
- `make certs` for mkcert TLS certificates (`*.modelo.dev`)
- `make setup` for full local setup (DNS check, certs, port check)
- `make check-dns` / `make check-ports` for diagnostics
- `make sync-keycloak-client` for Keycloak client alignment

Anti-Patterns:

- NEVER run node/bun/npm/pip directly on host — use containers
- Avoid exposing service ports directly — route through Traefik
- Avoid hardcoded container names in code — use Docker DNS
